<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> heard it from the horse’s mouth • little bird told me, a</xh5><p> <i>heard it from the horse’s mouth—</i>heard it directly from the person concerned: The story was even more intriguing when we <u>heard it from the horse’s mouth</u>.</p><p> <i>little bird told me, a—</i>said of information gathered from a source not to be named: <u>A little bird told</u> me that the appointment of a director will be made shortly.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>go tell it to the birds</b>—<i>addressed to a person who says smth. that is not credible or is a lie: </i>After this incident, it might be difficult to dismiss some witchcraft claims with the expression, “<u>go tell it to the birds</u>!”</p> </entry>
